(firstQuint)Use of Allogenic Platelet Lysate in Peripheral Arterial Disease (PAD).

 Allogenic platelet rich plasma (PRP) will be collected from blood group AB donors.

 This plasma will be tested for the presence of any chronic infectious blood borne disease.

 Platelet lysate will be then prepared from the tested PRP to be intramuscularly injected in patients with PAD.

